               <p>MISS GRIFFITHS. I am sister to Mrs. Griffiths. I know they are my sister's things.</p>
               <p>ELIZABETH WALKER. I take in needle-work. The prisoner brought these things to me to make up into articles for herself. The child's bonnet she tell<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181407060013"></xptr>me was her perquisite. The muslin she told me to make into caps.</p>
